<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai, Yunnan to Strengthen Economic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 26 (Xinhua) -- China's largest city Shanghai
will strengthen economic ties with Yunnan Province in southwest
China, according to a cooperation outline signed recently by the
two sides.
</P>
<P>
The two have agreed on 30 cooperation projects which involve a
joint investment of more than two billion yuan (about 241 million
US dollars), and another 60 projects the two sides intend to
complete jointly.
</P>
<P>
Last June, the State Council, the country's highest governing
body, decided that Shanghai, with its talented workforce, advanced
technology and abundant investment capital, would come to the aid
of underdeveloped Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
Over the next several years, Shanghai and Yunnan will increase
cooperation in fields involving metallurgy, machinery and
electronics, and non-ferrous metals, as well as the chemical
industry, and the light and textile industries.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the two sides will focus on setting up a large
steel plant in Yunnan to promote the growth of some related
businesses.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai is encouraging some machine, cable and power equipment
producers to find cooperative partners in Yunnan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
