<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, January 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli parliamentarians, both from the ruling
Likud and opposition Labor parties, signed a joint position paper,
permitting the establishment of a Palestinian entity whose status
will be determined in future negotiations.
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Afghan warring factions issued a declaration on a
conference held here, urging all Afghan groups to cooperate for
cessation of hostilities and preservation of independence,
territorial integrity and national unity.
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- A British patrol car was blasted off in Ballynahich,
Northern Ireland, slightly wounding a British soldier and adding
up the number of such attacks to eight.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Six people were killed and 35 others injured when
a bus plunged into a river from a bridge after colliding with a
truck in India's Gujarat state on Saturday, according to the local
press.
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Moldovan parliament today approved Prime Minister
Ion Ciubuc's new government, which was sworn in at an inaugural
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- An international conference on combat against
poverty and social exclusion will be held in San Jose from January
28 to 30, the Costa Rican Foreign Ministry announced
Saturday. 
</P>
