<HEADLINE> New Stamps on Sale in Hong Kong to Replace Old Designs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 26 (Xinhua) -- A set of new definitive
stamps went on sale here today to replace the old designs bearing
Queen Elizabeth's head.
</P>
<P>
The old designs bearing the portrait of the British Queen were
withdrawn from general sale at the close of business on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Post offices across Hong Kong opened today to sell the new
stamps, which feature Hong Kong Island's famous skyline.
</P>
<P>
The new stamps can be used before and after July 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
Graphic Designer Kan Tai-keung, creative director of Kan and
Lau Design Consultants, has been designing stamps for the post
office since 1960. He was selected to design the new definitive
stamps two years ago.
</P>
<P>
"I feel very honored and happy to be selected to design the
stamps for the new government," he was quoted by the local
English-language newspaper South China Morning Post as saying.
</P>
<P>
"I chose the harbor because it is one of the most beautiful
scenes of Hong Kong," Kan said.
</P>
<P>
The 13 designs depict Victoria Harbor and Hong Kong Island from
east to west during daylight hours, while the three high-priced
stamps valued at 10, 20 and 30 HK dollars show the Hong Kong
skyline at night.
</P>
<P>
The illustrations are taken from photos and the shades have
been computer-enhanced.
</P>
<P>
A set of Hong Kong's Special Administrative Region stamps are
expected to be issued on June 30 this year to commemorate the
handover.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
