<HEADLINE> Chechens Ready for Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Chechnya, a local republic
trying to break away from the Russian Federation, is ready for
presidential and parliamentary elections, which are scheduled for
Monday.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 polling stations representing over 60
constituencies had been prepared for the elections, in which 14
candidates will run for the presidency and 833 candidates will
contest the 63 mandates to the parliament, according to reports
reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Over 70 foreign observers representing the Organization for
Security and Cooperation in Europe have arrived in Chechnya to
monitor the forthcoming elections. The elections will be covered
by over 200 Russian and foreign reporters gathering in Grozny,
capital of Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
Analysts here predicted that five candidates, including Aslan
Maskhadov, Zelimkhan Yandarbiyev, Shamir Basayev, Movladi Udugov
and Akhmed Zakayev, enjoy the best chances to win the presidential
elections. But the major rivals are Maskahdov and Basayev, experts
cited recent public opinion polls as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
