<HEADLINE> Syrian Vice President, FM Visit Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Vice President
Abdul-Halim Khaddam and Foreign Minister Farouq al-Shara arrived
in Saudi Arabia today on a visit which had not been officially
announced.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait News Agency (KUNA) reported that the two Syrian
officials were greeted at the Riyadh International Airport by
Saudi Prince and Deputy Prime Minister Prince Abdullah Ibn
Abdul-Aziz and a number of princes and officials including
Foreign Minister Saud Al-Faisal Al-Saud.
</P>
<P>
No official comments were made in Riyadh, the Saudi capital,
on the aims of the visit or whether a letter from Syrian
President Hafez Assad will be delivered to Saudi King Fahd Ibn
Abdul-Aziz, KUNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The visit came amid a flurry of meetings among Arab leaders in
Riyadh after the signing of the Hebron agreement by the
Palestinian National Authority and Israel earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
King Hussein of Jordan visited Saudi Arabia Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa also
concluded a two-day visit to the Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Moussa conveyed a letter from Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
to King Fahd over the Middle East peace process, the
developments in Sudan and bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, Egypt and Syria were the three major Arab
countries that launched the Arab summit in Cairo last year to
coordinate the Arabian attitude towards Israel after the Israeli
right-wing Likud government suspended the Middle East peace
process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
