<HEADLINE> Supply, Marketing Cooperatives Urged to Serve Expansion of Rural Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Federation of
Supply and Marketing Cooperatives should expand rural markets, so
as to give full scope to the initiative of farmers, a senior
Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Only when farmers can completely sell out their agricultural
products can they have the purchase power to buy more industrial
goods, which in turn helps the rural economy to achieve overall
development, said State Councillor Chen Junsheng, who is also head
of the federation's council.
</P>
<P>
Chen noted that in the past, the central government has carried
out a series of policies to ensure the sustained and steady
development of agriculture. Additionally, he said, the state has
raised the purchasing prices of grain on a big margin to benefit
farmers.
</P>
<P>
Consecutive crop harvests and the subsequent growing income of
farmers over the years have provided the supply and marketing
cooperatives with the opportunity for expanding rural markets,
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
With their increasing purchasing power, the farmers can buy
more and more industrial consumer goods, and the national economy,
as a whole, can grow in a healthy way.
</P>
<P>
Such supply and marketing cooperatives at various levels all
across the country are obligated to help farmers to promote their
products through expanding their business scope, Chen said.
</P>
</TEXT>
