<HEADLINE> Egypt, Gambia Begin Talks in Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
and Gambian President Yahya Jammeh today opened a preliminary
round of talks on bilateral relations here at the presidential
residence Kubba Palace.
</P>
<P>
Official talks between the two presidents are expected to begin
tomorrow at a working Iftar, the Moslem fast breaking meal at
dusk, Mubarak will host in honor of his Gambian guest.
