<HEADLINE> HK Police Arrest Six Suspects in Connection With </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong police today
arrested six suspects in connection with the murder and arson case
from a fire that killed 15 people at a karaoke club in Tsim Sha
Tsui early Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
Following an in-depth investigation into the case, Hog Kong
Police's Organized Crime and Triad Bureau (OCTB) officers have
identified a group of 11 suspects, including nine men and two
women.
</P>
<P>
Police then arrested four men and two women, aged between 17
and 28, in Ma Tau Kok, Kwun Tong and Tseung Kwan O.
</P>
<P>
Police are looking for the remaining five men who are still at
large.
</P>
<P>
Police also arrested a 20-year-old male bouncer of the karaoke
club who is suspected to be in connection with an unreported
assault case which occurred recently inside the club.
</P>
<P>
The bouncer and a 38-year-old man arrested on Saturday for the
case are being detained for questioning, police said.
</P>
<P>
A fierce fire broke out at the club early Saturday morning,
killing 15 people and injuring 15 others.  
</P>
</TEXT>
