<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Flood Victims to Receive Relief Maize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Flood victims in Lundazi and
Chama districts of Zambia's Eastern Province are receiving 192
tons of maize from the Prevention Against Malnutrition (PAM),
Zambia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Floods devastated the local people's maize fields and other
food crops during the 1995/96 farming season.
</P>
<P>
PAM Eastern Provincial Coordinator Edify Hamukale said in
Chipata, capital of Eastern Province today that the PAM is also
distributing a total of 85 tons of maize, sorghum, cow peas,
groundnuts and sunflower seeds to all districts in the province
on loan to help farmers there invest in food production.
</P>
<P>
However, Hamukale said the delivery of the relief food to
the affected areas should not raise hopes for people living on
the plateau whose food crops were not swept by floods that they
will also be given food by the government.
</P>
<P>
He urged them to take up farming seriously to boost food
production instead of waiting for handouts from the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
