<HEADLINE> Aidid, UN Mend Their Fences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Somali faction leader
Hussein Aidid announced today that his faction has reached an
understanding agreement with the United Nations to end the
longstanding friction between them.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a rally in South Mogadishu's main stadium on the
sixth anniversary of the toppling of the late regime of Siad
Barre, Hussein Aidid said his faction is optimistic to get remedy
for what's done in the past, but he did not give details.
</P>
