<HEADLINE> Commercial Bank of Ethiopia Increases Credit Fund </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- The Commercial Bank of
Ethiopia said today that the fund set aside for credit in the
past five years has grown from 364 million to 3.4 billion Birr
(6.4 Birr equal to one U.S.Dollar ).
</P>
<P>
The Assistant Vice-President of the Credit Assessment and
Analysis Department of the bank, Mulugeta Bebremedhin, told the
local press that 834 percent credit growth was attained due to
the rise in the number of debtors following the economic reform
and the expansion of services by the bank.
</P>
<P>
Mulugeta said that demand for credit has grown thanks to
production boosting witnessed in government development agencies,
the need created for more inputs in the agricultural secfor, and
the involvement of enterpreneurs in various sectors of the
economy.
</P>
<P>
The betterment in the financial status of farmers has
subsquently contributed for growth in demand for commodities
which in turn has spurred industrial activities aimed at
benefitting from the thriving market, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to the bank, credit service for the agricultural
sector has grown from 2 million to 317 million Birr with that of
the industry and domestic trade sectors showing a rise in the
stated period from 80 million to 290 million Birr and 199 million
to 2 billion Birr respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
