<HEADLINE> Strange killer Disease Identified in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 26 (Xinhua) -- A strange disease, which had
killed 22 people in Zambia's Southern Province during the past
two weeks, has been identified as a combination of bubonic plague
and pneumonic plague.
</P>
<P>
A medical investigative team, which was dispatched to the area
after the outbreak of the strange disease, announced here today
that the disease was caused by dead rats in the wells.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 22 people killed by the disease, 14 died in their
homes before receiving treatment and the rest died while
undergoing treatment at the health centers. 
</P>
