<HEADLINE>   Sudan Forms Emergency Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese President General
Omar El-Bashir issued a decree today to form a high commission
for emergence and general mobilization.
</P>
<P>
The commission, which is under Bashir's first deputy General
El-Zubeir Mohamed Saleh, comprises of a large number of
ministers, executive officials and public figures, according to
the presidential decree.
</P>
<P>
It will arrange the general mobilization to face up to the
dangers and plots that are being engineered against Sudan. It will
also determine the potentials of the people and make best use of
them in defense of the country.
</P>
<P>
The commission will work to consolidate the internal front,
collect information that can serve the aims of the internal and
external media, and raise the financial and moral support for the
armed forces, police and civil defense.
</P>
<P>
It will also promote the Jihad (holy war) spirit among all
walks of life in Sudan.
</P>
<P>
The decree of setting up the emergency commission came when
fighting between the government forces and rebels is going on in
the eastern province of the Blue Nile which borders
Ethiopia. Sudanese government has accused Ethiopia and Eritrea of
involvement in the two-week long battles, but the claim has been
rejected by the two countries. 
</P>
