<TEXT>
<P>
Phnom Penh, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The four-day Extraordinary
General Assembly of the Cambodian People's Party (CPP) finished
this afternoon after adopting a four-point resolution.
</P>
<P>
The resolution said the General Assembly unanimously adopted
the CPP political platform concerning national rehabilitation and
development for the years ahead.
</P>
<P>
The platform defined the CPP principles and perspectives for
building Cambodia into a kingdom of independence, peace, freedom,
democracy, neutrality and social progress.
</P>
<P>
The CPP is one of Cambodia's four ruling parties.
</P>
<P>
The CPP's Chairman, Chea Sim, who doubles as the president of
the National Assembly of Cambodia, delivered a closing speech at
the assembly.
</P>
