<HEADLINE> China Enjoys Stable Situation in Int'l Income, Payment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- China is now enjoying the
comfort of a stable international income and payment situation, a
senior Chinese official said here today.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China's foreign exchange situation maintained a sound
development trend, along with the remarkable achievements in the
country's macro-economic control and the evident improvement of
the economic and financial situation, according to Zhou Xiaochuan,
Director of the State Administration of Foreign Exchange (SAFE).
</P>
<P>
Speaking today at a national conference attended by heads of
SAFE's provincial branches, he said that China's imports and
exports totaled 289.9 billion US dollars last year, with a surplus
of 12.24 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The overseas funds which actually arrived were more than 50
billion US dollars, including a direct overseas investment of
42.35 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Also last year, China witnessed a slow-down in the growth of
its outstanding overseas debts as the sum increased only nine
percent to reach 116.28 billion US dollars, 9.69 billion US
dollars more than that of the previous year, Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
He estimated that there would be balanced international incomes
and payments under current accounts, with a little surplus, while
there would be a relatively big surplus for capital accounts.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, supply was larger than demand in the local foreign
exchange market, while the state foreign exchange reserve
increased by a large margin to top 105 billion US dollars, up
31.4 billion US dollars over the figure at the beginning of the
year, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate of the RMB yuan against the US dollar climbed
from 8.3174 to 8.2984, increasing at a slower rate compared with
the previous two years.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said that the rise in China's foreign exchange reserve has
largely contributed to the country's comprehensive overseas
payment capacity. It has also laid a relatively solid foundation
for continuing the reforms, and has helped to inspire foreign
investors' confidence in the country's economic development.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
