<HEADLINE> Baiul Scheduled for Court Appearance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Oksana
Baiul was scheduled to face charges at West Harford Superior Court
Monday that she was driving drunk and recklessly when she crashed
her Mercedes earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Baiul, 19, of Ukraine, was arrested by Bloomfield police
January 14 and charged with driving under the influence and
reckless driving.
</P>
<P>
Bloomfield police estimate that Baiul was driving up to 97 mph
when her car skidded off a two-lane road about 2:25 a.m. on
January 12, while she was returning to her home in Simsbury after
a night out in Hartford.
</P>
<P>
Officers smelled a "very strong odor" of alcohol on Baiul's
breath at the accident scene, according to a police affidavit. An
officer who briefly interviewed her at the hospital at 9
a.m. January 13 also reported smelling alcohol on her breath.
</P>
<P>
Baiul sustained a cut scalp and a concussion in the accident.
Ari Zakarian, a fellow skater who was a passenger in the car,
sustained minor injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
