<HEADLINE> DC High Voltage Transmission Project Signed in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The equipment contract of the
Tiansheng DC High Voltage Transmission Project, meant to alleviate
the power shortage in Guangdong Province, was concluded here today.
</P>
<P>
Signing the agreement were representatives from the China
National Technical Import and Export Corporation (CNTIEC), the
South China Power Integrated Company and the Siemens Company of
Germany.
</P>
<P>
The Tiansheng project is being carried out at the Tiansheng
Bridge Hydroelectric Station, which is located at the conjuncture
of Guangxi, Yunnan and Guizhou provinces.
</P>
<P>
The auxiliary project is designed to transmit the electricity
of the hydroelectric station and the surplus power produced by
Yunnan and Guizhou provinces from the Tiansheng Bridge to
Guangzhou, the capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
As trustee of the South China Power Integrated Company, CNTIEC
purchased the converter equipment of the transmission project with
credit granted by Japan's Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund
through international bidding. The bid was won by Siemens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
