<HEADLINE> More US Congressmen Visit China to Bridge Two Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- With the ongoing improvement in
China-US relations, more and more US congressmen have come to visit
China in hopes of presenting a more informal view of the
dramatically-changing country to their constituents back home.
</P>
<P>
Rep. Gary Ackerman, one of the 30-strong US congressmen to
visit China already this year, met with Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen this afternoon, and both sides agreed
that the increasing number of visits to China on the part of US
congressmen will help boost mutual understanding and bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Ackerman, the senior Democratic House Representative in charge
of Asian-Pacific affairs, also conferred with Qian on Sino-US
relations and international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Ackerman is here as guest of the Chinese People's Institute of
Foreign Affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
