<HEADLINE> Cantona Banned for Two Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Manchester United's Eric Cantona
has been suspended for two matches after being booked in
Saturday's F.A. Cup tie against Wimbledon.
</P>
<P>
He will have to sit out United's premier league clash at
Arsenal on February 19 and could miss a potential fifth round
F.A. Cup match against first division Queens Park Rangers on the
preceeding weekend.
</P>
<P>
The suspension is the Frenchman's first in the two years since
he was banned for an infamous assault on a Crystal Palace fan
during a match in January 1995. 
</P>
