<HEADLINE> China to Promote Parliamentary Relations with Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- China and Greece, two of the
world's ancient civilizations, will promote parliamentary
exchanges with each other, Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen
said here today.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with a Greek parliament delegation led by
Karolos Papoulias, chairman of the Foreign Affairs and Defense
Committee of the parliament, Qiao, also Chinese vice-premier, said
that exchanges between China and Greece are of great significance
politically, economically and culturally.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the friendship between the two
countries will continue to advance.
</P>
<P>
Papoulias said that China, as a major world peace-keeping
force, has been playing an increasingly vital role in the
international affairs. He hopes that China, as a permanent member
of the UN Security Council, will have a greater impact on regional
and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides also exchanged views on
issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The Greek delegation arrived here Sunday for a week-long visit
as guests of the Standing Committee of Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC). 
</P>
</TEXT>
