<DOCNO> XIE19970127.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Japan to Build Fertilizer Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Japan will jointly
build a NPK (nitrogen, phosporus and potassium) fertilizer plant
in the Go Dau industrial zone, Dong Nai province, in south Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The local media said the project, with a total investment of
39.75 million U.S. dollars, was a 30-year joint venture between
the Nissho Iwai Corporation of Vietnam and the Central Glass
Co. Ltd of Japan.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese company was committed to transferring technology
and know-how to the joint venture, to produce fertilizer up to
international standards.
</P>
<P>
The plant is expected to go into operation in the final quarter
of 1998 with a designed annual capacity of 350,000 tons of NPK
fertilizer, which is suitable for various soil conditions.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese partners have committed 70 percent of the total
capital of 14 million U.S. dollars, while the remaining 30 percent
stake, worth 2.8 million dollars, is provided by the Vietnamese
partner in the form of a land use agreement of 15 hectares for 19
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
