<HEADLINE> UN Health Care Success in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A health care program initiated
by the United Nations World Food Program (WFP) has been
implemented effectively in Vietnam, the local media reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The 10 million U.S. dollar project mainly covers the 456
communes of Vietnam's mountain provinces.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, which started in June 1995, about 80 percent
of expectant mothers there were given medical check-ups, and more
than 73 percent were vaccinated twice against tetanus.
</P>
<P>
Of the under-three-year-old children, 80 percent were regularly
weighed and given medical examinations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
