<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Eastern Airlines Listing To Raise 250 Million US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 27 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Airlines
Co. Ltd., one of the largest air carriers in the Chinese inland
areas, announced here today a new issue through a combined
offering of 1.4 billion shares, to raise up to 1.9 billion HK
dollars (250 million US dollars) in gross proceeds.
</P>
<P>
The subscription price is between 1.22 and 1.38 HK dollars per
H share in Hong Kong, or between 16 and 18 US dollars per American
Depository Share (ADS). Each ADS represents 100 of the company's H
shares.
</P>
<P>
The combined offering includes three tranches: the Hong Kong
public offering, initially representing 10 percent of the
offering, the US offering initially representing 45 percent, and
the international offering initially representing 45 percent.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of the Hong Kong offering will increase to a
maximum of 30 percent of the total global offering, if the Hong
Kong tranche is over-subscribed by ten times or more.
</P>
<P>
Application forms will be available on Tuesday and the latest
time for lodging applications will be by noon of Friday. The final
share price is expected to be fixed on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Trading in ADSs on the New York Stock Exchange is scheduled to
commence on February 4, while dealing in H shares on the Hong Kong
Stock Exchange is scheduled to commence on February 5.
</P>
<P>
About 60 percent of the net proceeds from the combined offering
will be used to acquire new aircraft and related spare parts and
equipment.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern Airlines operates 114 routes, 91 of which are
domestic, and makes over 1,100 scheduled flights per week from 44
airports within China and abroad.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey conducted by the Civil Aviation
Administration of China, the company ranked number one among all
Chinese airlines in management, service quality and on-time
performance in 1993, 1994 and 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
