<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Residents Top World in Fruit Consumption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Official statistics show that
the Hong Kong people are the world's No. 1 consumer of fruits in
terms of per capita average.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months of 1996, Hong Kong imported more than
800,000 tons of fruits, which means that Hong Kong's six million
residents consume over 2,500 tons of fruits each day on an
average.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong relies imports for fruit consumption. Last year it
paid over seven billion HK dollars (897 million US dollars) on
fruits, 10 percent more than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Major fruit suppliers to Hong Kong are the United States,
Thailand and the Chinese inland areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
