<HEADLINE> Hundreds of Shops Gutted by Fire in Jakarta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of shops and
restaurants at the eight-story Harco shopping complex in Pasar
Baru (new market), central Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, were
razed by a fire this morning, Antara news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which started at about 6 a.m. local time, was
believed to have been caused by a short-circuit in the second
floor of the building.
</P>
<P>
The fire was not easy to control as almost all of the shops
were full of flammable goods, mostly textile and textile products,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
The raze went on for at least seven hours, spreading further to
burn nearby offices and stores.
</P>
<P>
No reports on casualties and material damages were available
yet.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the evening newspaper "Suara Pembaruan" said some 200
stalls were destroyed by the fire.  
</P>
</TEXT>
