<HEADLINE> China Launchs First CDMA Product Line in Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- China's first assembly line for
CDMA (code diversion multiple accesses) products, the
new-generation mobile telecommunications mode, has gone into
operation in Hangzhou, capital of Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based Science and Technology Daily said that the
production line was built at Hangzhou Motorola Mobile Telephone
System Ltd., a Sino-Motorola joint venture, and will be able to
turn out 500 SC2450 CDMA systems by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
CDMA is the most advanced mobile telecommunications mode in the
world in term of its transmission capacity and frequency use rate.
It is believed to be a potential substitute to the present GSM
(global service for mobile communication) standard.
</P>
<P>
So far, China has launched two pilot CDMA networks in Fujian
and Guangdong Provinces, based on equipment from Motorola and
Lucent Technologies, the former network and system business of
AT&AMP;T.
</P>
<P>
Last December, Motorola signed an agreement with a Beijing
telecom company to install a CDMA network in Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
