<HEADLINE> Finnish Telecom Company Help Yunnan Expand GSM Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan
Province has signed a contract with a joint venture of Nokia, the
leading Finnish mobile telecom supplier, for a major expansion of
the province's digital mobile telephone network.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation agreement was clinched by the province's posts
and telecommunications administration and Beijing Nokia Mobile
Telecom Ltd., Science and Technology Daily reported in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
When completed, the project will raise the province's GSM
(global service for mobile communication) switching capacity to
200,000 handsets.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, Beijing Nokia will begin to supply
Yunnan with GSM digital system products and equipment for a
service center from next month.
</P>
<P>
Nokia has maintained a leading place in the province's mobile
telephone market for two years, said the paper. Launched last May,
the province's first GSM network was also based on Nokia
equipment. The Finnish company expanded the network in the second
half of 1996.  
</P>
