<HEADLINE> Nigerian Soccer National Coach Sacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's soccer authority has
dismissed national coach Amodu Shaibu, who was suspended at the
weekend, officials announced here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Austin Mgbolu, spokesman of the Nigeria Football Association
(NFA), said that the NFA has sacked Amodu Shaibu for "gross
misconduct, insubordination and making embarrassing remarks about
its activities and the person of the sports minister."
</P>
<P>
Shaibu was suspended at the weekend on the orders of sports
minister Jim Nwobodo.
</P>
<P>
Mgbolu said the dismissal took immediate effect. The spokeman
added that his association had not yet considered naming another
local coach to replace Shaibu.
</P>
<P>
The relationship between Shaibu and the sports authorities has
not been smooth since October when he was told to take temporary
charge of the national team while a permanent replacement was
sought for former manager Jo Bonfrere.
</P>
<P>
The Dutchman quit the job in October alleging poor treatment
and interference in his duties by the sports authorities.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria was held to a 1-1 tie with Kenya in Nairobi in a World
Cup qualifier two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
The draw placed the Olympic champions into second position
behind Guinea in a World Cup group of four teams from which one
will qualify for the finals in France next year.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria will host Guinea on April 5 in their next World Cup
qualifier. 
</P>
</TEXT>
