<HEADLINE> Consternation on FDI Affects India's Focus: Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The consternation over
foreign direct investment (FDI) has kept India as a marginal
player among the developing world, Industry Secretary N. Mohanty
said.
</P>
<P>
"There is so much consternation over FDI due to the East India
Company syndrome. India is still a marginal player and does not
even figure among the top ten developing nations in terms of
investment flow," Press Trust of India (PTI) quoted him as saying
here today.
</P>
<P>
Emphasizing the need for a "national consensus" on the issue of
foreign investment, the industry secretary said, "we need to make
up our minds whether we need FDI or not. If some people have
doubts, government should take a majority view."
</P>
<P>
"India is not focused on FDI like China," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
