<HEADLINE> International Conference on Drug Abuse Opens in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The 2nd International
Conference on Drug Abuse opened in Shatin Town Hall here today
with the attendance of experts and professionals from 12 countries
and regions.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Chinese University of Hong Kong, the four-day
conference aims to exchange experiences among clinicians,
scientists, sociologists, educators and social workers of the
drug-control circle.
</P>
<P>
Alfred Stadlin, organizer of the conference, said that as there
is an increase in drug abuse in Asia, the conference aims to raise
public awareness of the psycho-social and biological effects of
drug abuse.
</P>
<P>
She noted that the conference will have an important impact on
Hong Kong and its neighboring countries as we are facing
escalating drug abuse problems and growing HIV-AIDS epidemic in
Asia.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, there will be a series of lectures and
symposiums on drug prevention and education, alcohol abuse and
related diseases, psycho-social aspects of drug abuse and drug
policies and legislation.
</P>
<P>
The 1st International Conference on Drug Abuse was held in
Portugal last April.
</P>
<P>
Among those who attended the meeting include experts from
universities in Beijing, Wuhan, Ningbo and Harbin.  
</P>
</TEXT>
