<HEADLINE> South Korea's Trading Firms to Expand Overseas Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, January 27 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's giant trading firms
plan to promote their overseas operations this year, industry
sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
Samsung Corporation has decided to push its overseas firms to
center on a number of projects, including power generation and
ranch projects in Vietnam, Australia and Middle East countries.
</P>
<P>
Samsung has also decided to promote large plant exports to
Africa and Eastern European countries to take advantage of the
company's takeover of the group's construction business in 1995.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Hyundai Corporation has shown interest in a
copper mine in Peru, an iron ore mine in Venezuela and other
resources development projects elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
Daewoo Corporation has been following a strategy to develop a
16.5-million-square-meter dairy ranch in Poland, an oil field in
Angola and a rubber plantation in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
LG International Corporation, meanwhile, is pursuing the
construction of oil refineries in Thailand and Vietnam, in
addition to property development projects in Indonesia being
promoted by LG Business Group as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Hyosung Corporation has decided to set up hot-rolled steel
plants in both China and Thailand and a textile plant in Vietnam.
</P>
