<HEADLINE> 200 Stalls Destroyed by Fire in Jakarta, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 200 stalls in a big
shopping complex in central Jakarta, capital of Indonesia, were
destroyed by a fire which started this morning, the evening
newspaper "Suara Penbaruan" reported.
</P>
<P>
The fire occurred in the Pasar Baru (new market) at 6:05 a.m.
local time, head of the Fire-Extinguishing Agency (DPK) Suharso
said.
</P>
<P>
He said the fire may have been caused by the rupture of a gas
pipe in a roast chicken restaurant near the shopping center.
</P>
<P>
The fire had not been completely extinguished as of this
afternoon, the report said.
</P>
<P>
No information on casualties were available right now.
</P>
