<HEADLINE> Heavy Industrial Center Attracts More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The leading heavy industrial
center of Anshan, in northeast China, set new records in its use
of overseas investments and promoting exports last year.
</P>
<P>
It absorbed a direct foreign investment of 97.41 million US
dollars in building 67 projects in 1996. Its export volume rose to
358 million US dollars, said a local trade official.
</P>
<P>
Key and large state-owned enterprises were encouraged to boost
export-oriented production. The Anshan Iron and Steel
Incorporation conducted technological cooperation with
counterparts in Germany and Japan.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the volume of its exported rolled steel soared to
735,000 tons last year, yielding 75 million yuan, 134 percent up
from the previous year's amount.
</P>
<P>
City officials have visited north and south America, Europe,
Asia, Australia and Africa to promote economic and trade
cooperation. Twelve of the 500 top companies in the world have
signed contracts with local enterprises.  
