<HEADLINE> Japan and Slovenia Split Titles on Snow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MUJU, South Korea, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Japan and Slovenia
split two gold medals on snow Monday at the World Winter
University Games.
</P>
<P>
Japan's 20 year old Otaka Tomomi came from a half way behind to
capture the women's 10 kilometers cross-country in 29:28.6,
beating five Russians to second to fifth places.
</P>
<P>
Natalia Massalkina, who led the first five kilometers by 20
seconds ahead of Tomomi, was timed of 29:29.9. Loulia Lementchouk
clocked 29:30 for the bronze medal, followed by Olga Zamorozova
and Natalia Novikova
</P>
<P>
With Tomomi's victory, Japan collected two golds in the games.
</P>
<P>
Among the field of over 40 skiers from 15 countries, China's
luan Zhengrong finished 11th with 30:47.8.
</P>
<P>
In the women's downhill, Slovenia took a 1-2 lead after Andreja
Potisk-Ribic won the gold medal with a time of 1:10.91 and Anja
Kalan silver in 1:11.03. American Katherine Davenport brought home
a bronze in 1:11.78. 
</P>
</TEXT>
