<HEADLINE> Major International Environment Forum in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The '97 China Environment
Forum, the first international environmental symposium sponsored
by non-governmental organizations in the country, will focus on
the coordinated development of China's economic, social, and
environmental sectors.
</P>
<P>
Results from the forum will contribute to new environmental
protection measures to be formulated by the Chinese government, Ye
Ruqiu, deputy director of the State Bureau of Environmental
Protection, said today at a press conference.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that environmental protection needs the
participation of society, and the forum itself shows that Chinese
people's awareness on environmental protection has improved.
</P>
<P>
With approval from the State Council, the '97 China
Environment Forum will be held in Beijing from the 24th to 27th of
next month.
</P>
<P>
The event will be sponsored by the Chinese Society for
Environmental Sciences and the Institute of Human Ecology, both
large non-governmental organizations focusing on environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
Represented will be authorities from the United Nations
Environment Program, well-known world experts and scholars in
environmental protection, and senior officials from Chinese
central and local governments and environmental departments,
according to Ye.
</P>
<P>
Ye said that the delegates will probe issues of
environmental legislation, trade and environment, biological
diversity, environmental education, comprehensive development
and utilization of energy, as well as the use of science and
technology in environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Simultaneously held will be exhibitions, exchanges, and program
negotiations on sciences, technology, and products of environmental
protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
