<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese City Plans to Move Mountain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese city plans to cure
its serious pollution problem by moving a mountain.
</P>
<P>
It will take two years to remove the 30 million cubic meters of
a mountain to the east of industrial Lanzhou, capital of Gansu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The removal of the three-hilltop mountain will cost around 100
million-yuan (12 million US dollars). The project has been
launched by the city government of Lanzhou to clear atmospheric
pollution and again bring the sight of clear blue skies to its
citizens.
</P>
<P>
Located in the basin of river valley, the city is surrounded by
mountains, which slows down atmospheric circulation and the
dispersal of pollutants.
</P>
<P>
To relieve the situation, the city government decided to change
the geographical conditions by leveling the Daqingshan mountain in
eastern part of the city. The project is expected to be finished
in two years, and more than 30 million cubic meters of earth will
be removed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
