<HEADLINE> Zambia's Mortality Rate Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's mortality rate has
dropped in recent years from a predicted 126 deaths to 109 deaths
per 1,000.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Minister of Health K. Kalumba when he
officially launched a health center here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
It is an achievement "in view of the economic position of most
of our people and the nation," he said. 
