<HEADLINE> First International Shipping Route for Jiangxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A container ship of the
Jianghai Ocean Shipping Company based in east China's Jiangxi
Province has successfully made its maiden international voyage.
</P>
<P>
It means the opening of the first ocean shipping route from the
Yangtze River for Jiangxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The 1,800-tonnage "Hongning", with a capacity of 62 containers,
will be mainly used to handle overseas and domestic container
transport in the future, company officials say.
</P>
<P>
The Jianghai Ocean Shipping Company, set up in 1990, mainly
handles cargo transport business at large and medium-sized sea
ports in Shanghai, China's largest economic center, and Hainan,
the southernmost island province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
