<HEADLINE> China to Sign Up 15 Million Telephone Clients in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The number of telephone
subscribers in China will increase by 15 million this year,
fortifying the country's status as an emerging telecom consumer in
the world, according to a senior official in the post and
telecommunications industry.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai-based Business News quoted Wu Jichuan, minister of
posts and telecommunications, as saying that by the end of 1997,
China's telephone availability rate will reach 7.4 percent, and
the country's integrated telecom strength will be further expanded.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the country's investment in the posts and
telecommunications sector will be accelerated, with the input on
the industry's fixed assets hitting 95 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the telephone switching capacity will increase by 17
million lines, and four million new clients will be added to the
mobile telephone subscription.
</P>
<P>
Along with the rapid growth of the industry, the telephone
density rate will hit 25 percent in urban areas, the paper said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
