<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The coastal city of Shenzhen
in south China's Guangdong Province will boost the bioengineering
industry as part of its effort to expand high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
City government statistics show that bioengineering industry
turned out 530 million yuan (63.86 million dollars) worth-of
products in 1996, up nearly 44 percent over the previous year. It
plans to raise its annual output value to five billion yuan by the
year 2000, according to a government official.
</P>
