of which have a large share of the domestic market. Hepatitis B
vaccine produced by the Kangtai Company, for example, in 1996
accounted for 70 percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, the city government has provided a
series of favorable funding and land use policies to the
industry. Banks have provided 300 million yuan in loans to support
bioengineering over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
A survey of 16 bioengineering enterprises has shown that their
total registered capital amounts to 560 million yuan and that they
have spent 692 million yuan in developing bioengineering
products.  
