<HEADLINE> Female Expert Makes Effective Anticarcinogen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- When 39-year-old cancer
patient John Chen was told that he had just one month to live, he
turned to traditional Chinese medicine as a miracle cure.
</P>
<P>
Twenty days after he began a medical regime prescribed by famed
Dr. Li Zhe, most of his symptoms had disappeared.
</P>
<P>
Chen is one of 103 cancer patients whose health has been
restored with Dr. Li's treatment.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Li grew up in a family with long and rich experiences of
traditional Chinese medicine. She began her career of fighting
cancer 20 years ago, when she successfully cured her own breast
cancer.
</P>
<P>
Over the past years, she has developed 17 types of cancer drugs
using traditional Chinese medicine, reporting a 92 percent
effectiveness rate.
</P>
<P>
Clinical observations show the tumors of 103 of her patients
have completely disappeared, and those of 751 have been diminished
or effectively controlled.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last year, Li Zhe was invited to the 2nd Annual
Oriental Medicine Conference USA. She won first prize for a paper
she presented, and was named honorary chairwoman and guest
professor by the Oriental Medicine Institute in America.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Li, who is president of the Anticancer Drugs Institute,
located in Changchun, the capital city of northeast China's Jilin
Province, believes she will continue to make more achievements in
the fight against cancer.
</P>
<P>
"In terms of curative effects for cancer, the traditional
Chinese medicine may be better than the Western medicine," she
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
