<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The streets of coastal Weihai in
east China's Shandong province offer a welcoming sign to the
city's fastest growing tourism group. Advertisements are not only
written in Chinese, but also Korean.
</P>
<P>
The small city, with a population of less than 300,000,
was the destination place for 67,000 tourists from ROK last year,
more than any other city in Shandong.
</P>
<P>
