<HEADLINE> Shanghai People Obsessed with British Universities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A special education exhibition
which ended on Sunday is expected to encourage more young people
from Shanghai to study in British universities.
</P>
<P>
The British Consulate sponsored the exhibition on the UK's
educational situation, with the hope that the coastal metropolis
will send more talented people to study in Great Britain, which
has a long educational history.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition offered full information on major British
universities and colleges, including the famous London University,
as well as the country's educational management and operational
systems.
</P>
<P>
The show was co-hosted by the Shanghai Educational Association
for International Exchanges, whose members believe that with 89
universities and colleges, Britain's high-quality educational
framework can serve as a useful reference for China's
modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Lectures were given during the two-day exhibition, which
attracted thousands of Shanghai people. Representatives from
British universities busily answered questions raised by curious
and studious Chinese youngsters.
</P>
<P>
The show also attracted educational workers and officials from
nearby provinces, who have been zealous for learning about the
world's most advanced educational methods.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,700 foreign students studied in Shanghai last year,
while 3,000 Shanghai people went abroad to study.
</P>
<P>
A total of 270,000 Chinese people have headed abroad for study
purposes since the late 1970s, and 90,000 of them have returned to
China.
</P>
<P>
Their favorite destinations include the United States and
Japan, as well as Great Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
