<HEADLINE> Low-Income Citizens of Tianjin Better Off </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Poorer off people in this port
city are being helped by municipal government price control and
aid-the-poor measures.
</P>
<P>
According to the authority, 105 price supervision stations have
been established in the city.
</P>
<P>
For some daily necessities, such as eggs and pork, retail price
ceilings are set by the authorities. A fund has also
been established to subsidize major commercial enterprises in the
city to help achieve stable market prices.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the retail price index in Tianjin increased by
5.1 percent last year, one of the lowest rises in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to an official at the municipal government, a total
of over 100 million Yuan (some 12 million US dollars) was spent
last year to help poor families in Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
"Some 350,000 people were employed or re-employed last year
with efforts made by the government", said the official.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the municipal government of Tianjin
last year completed 184 projects for relatively poor people in the
city to help them live a better life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
