<HEADLINE> Foreign Asphalt Mixing Plant Transformed for Local Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A high-grade asphalt mixing plant
imported from Britain has been transformed to meet local
road-building requirements.
</P>
<P>
The M3000 mobile asphalt mixing plant was jointly introduced
into China by the Ministry of Communications and the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, in a move to promote a
massive road construction drive in China.
</P>
<P>
Its main design and manufacturing techniques were imported from
the UK company, Parker Plant Ltd. The plant has a mixing capacity
of 250 tons an hour.
</P>
<P>
The transformation work was done by the Xi'an Road Construction
Machinery Factory in northwest China's Shaanxi Province. According
to experts, the transformed machine halved the price of their imported
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The road construction machinery factory, attached to the
Ministry of Communications, was set up in 1959, and has some 100
million yuan in fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
Its products are sold to the Republic of Korea, Singapore, Hong
Kong and Indonesia. It started to import asphalt mixing plants
from Britain and Germany, and transform them for local use in
1985. 
</P>
</TEXT>
