<HEADLINE> Indian Prime Minister to Visit Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Indian Prime Minister Deve
Gowda is to visit Russia early next month for enhancing the ties
between the two countries, highly placed sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The date for the trip to Moscow has not yet been finalized, but
if all goes well, he would leave for the Russian Federation on
February 13.
</P>
<P>
In Moscow, the prime minister will hold talks with Russian
President Boris Yeltsin and other Russian leaders on bilateral
relations and regional and international issues of mutual concern.
The current status of Russia-China ties and Sino-Indian relations
are items high on the agenda besides Afghanistan, the same sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The fact that Gowda has chosen to be in Moscow after his recent
visit to Bangladesh is reflective of the importance attached by
New Delhi to its ties with Russia.
</P>
<P>
Indian External Affairs Minister I. K. Gujral is going to be in
Moscow ahead of the prime minister for a meeting of the
Indo-Russian Joint Commission. He will stay on in the Russian
capital to be present during the prime minister's visit to Russia.
</P>
<P>
Originally, Gujral was to leave for Moscow on January 28 but
President Yeltsin's health and the preoccupation of the
Commonwealth of Independent States necessitated a change in his
schedule, the sources added.  
</P>
