<HEADLINE> Expert Group for MNC Role in Defense Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- A high-power study group
consisting of experts from both the government and private
sectors, has recommended large-scale participation of
multinational companies (MNCs) and domestic industrialists in
defense production.
</P>
<P>
The group has arrived at the consensus that open participation
of MNCs would have no adverse impact on the country's security
concerns and has suggested that there should be no inhibition from
the part of the government in inviting MNCs "case by case" to
areas such as the strategic electronics sector.
</P>
<P>
The group has recommended that those multinationals which hold
critical technology and are willing to transfer the same, should
be invited to participate in the defense sector.
</P>
<P>
The group in its suggestions said that in the given scenario of
India's strategic environment, the country has no alternative but
to vigorously pursue plans of expanding the defense industrial
base with the active participation of the domestic private
industrial sector and multinationals.  
</P>
</TEXT>
