<HEADLINE> Week-Long Royal Celebrations to Be Staged in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Nepal is to organize a
week-long celebration program here to mark the 25th anniversary of
King Birendra's accession to the throne in a grand manner,
official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The celebrations are expected to start with a grand civic
reception at a stadium in Downtown Kathmandu on January 31 when
the king will accept congratulation from Prime Minister Sher
Bahadur Deuba, who is chairman of a main celebration committee
comprising high-ranking government officials.
</P>
<P>
King Birendra will address the reception to be attended by
government officials, diplomats and people from all walks of life,
officials of the celebration committee said.
</P>
<P>
According to the committee, police and army personnel will
shower flowers from helicopters and balloons and pigeons will be
released on the occasion of the grand function where a variety of
cultural shows will also be staged.
</P>
<P>
The celebration program is to last for one week till February 6
when the prime minister will host a reception in honor of the king
and royal family members, the committee said.
</P>
<P>
During the celebration week, various religious organizations
will perform worship services at shrines and temples in Kathmandu
praying for the king's long life and the government will release
prison inmates with amnesty for their remaining terms, it added.
</P>
<P>
The government will also hold a function on February 5 to name
the International Convention Center in Kathmandu after the king
before organizing a group lamp-lighting program on the main street
in front of the royal palace.
</P>
<P>
On February 6, the state-run Nepal Television will present a
special documentary on the king and all museums in the country
will allow free entry for visitors to mark the end of the
celebrations, the committee said.
</P>
<P>
King Birendra came to the throne on January 31, 1972.  
</P>
</TEXT>
