<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Metrobank Becomes Philippines' Largest Conglomerate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 27 (Xinhua) -- After decades of being the
country's largest commercial bank, the Philippine National Bank
has given way to Metrobank, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The reports said Metrobank's assets grew by 26 percent to 200
billion pesos (7.6 billion U.S. dollars) last year, dislodging the
Philippine National Bank which posted total assets of 189 billion
pesos (7.2 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
While several of the country's big banks were products of some
mergers and consolidations, Metrobank had been piling up assets on
its own.
</P>
<P>
Metrobank, which overtook Bank of the Philippine Islands to be
the biggest private commercial bank several years ago, also led in
terms of loans and capital last year, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The bank had total deposits of 140 billion pesos (5.3 billion
dollars) as of the end of last December, followed by the
Philippine National Bank, Bank of the Philippine Islands and
PCIbank.  
</P>
</TEXT>
