<HEADLINE> New Navy Commander Appointed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chief of Staff of the Navy
Rear Admiral Cecil Tissera has been appointed the commander of the
Sri Lanka Navy with effect from today, according to an official
release from the Presidential Secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The release said Tissera becomes the 13th commander of the Sri
Lanka Navy and the first Navy commander to have been trained as an
officer cadet at Sri Lanka's Naval and Maritime Academy in
Trincomalee.
</P>
<P>
He was enlisted to the then Royal Ceylon Navy in September 1966
 and was selected as one of the academy's first officer cadets in
July 1969.
</P>
<P>
Tissera, 49, is also the youngest to assume command in the rank
of vice admiral.
</P>
<P>
He had been the chief of staff at the Naval Headquarters from
1993 and was promoted to be rear admiral on March 1, 1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
