<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finland Opposes Power Concentration of EU </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Finnish Minister of European
Affairs Ole Norrback today rejected a proposal calling for
enlarging the power of France, Germany and Britain within the
European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Norrback said the removal of veto power of some EU members will
not raise the efficiency of the EU's decision-making. On the
contrary, this will increase difficulty in cooperation within the
EU and could even possibly halt its ongoing integration process.
</P>
<P>
Hans Borek, a member in charge of external relations of the
Commission of the EU, proposed Saturday that small member
countries of the EU hand over their decision-making powers to
France, Germany and Britain, so as to quicken the pace of the EU's
decision-making process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
