<HEADLINE> New Shopping Mall to Promote Commercial Projects Along Yangtze </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Work has been completed on the
Ningbo Commercial Mansion, built at a cost of 400 million yuan and
the largest shopping mall in the history of this port city in east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
As one of the largest projects launched by the Yangtze Economic
Joint Development (Group) Corp., the newly-finished mall shows
that another important step has been made in the program to build
a commercial and trade corridor along the Yangtze River valley.
</P>
<P>
The project was initiated by the group, which is the leading
government-sponsored business in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The group has total assets of 2.5 billion yuan, with funds from
31 city governments, more than 50 large enterprises, and 28
branches of the Shanghai-based Bank of Communications in the
valley, said Gu Chuanxun, chairman of the group and a former vice
mayor of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Gu noted the group plans to establish a commercial and trade
corridor, with Shanghai as the leader, which is expected to help
promote economic growth in the Yangtze River valley, one of the
most economically developed areas in China.
</P>
<P>
With Ningbo as a strong link in its investment chain, the group
has also channeled funds to other main cities in the valley,
including Wuhan, Nanjing and Suzhou.
</P>
<P>
Local officials from both Shanghai and Ningbo praised the
project as an example of cooperation between the two cities.
</P>
</TEXT>
