<HEADLINE> Sweden's Karlsson Equals World Swimming Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 26 (Xinhua) -- Louise Karlsson of Sweden
equaled her world short course record in the women's 100-meter
medley, clocking one minute 1.03 seconds in a World Cup meet in
Malmo on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
She had set the record at the Esbo World Cup in Finland on
November 22, 1992.
</P>
<P>
In the men's 800 meters freestyle, Germany's Jorg Hoffmann
broke one of the oldest European records with a time of 7:36.24.
Michael Gross of Germany had set the old mark of 7:38.75 at Bonn
12 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Karlsson, 22, competed here this weekend for the first time
since taking a seven-month break after the Atlanta Olympics
because of bronchitis problems.
</P>
<P>
Since the 100 medley isn't a medal event in the World Short
Course Championships at Gothenburg, Sweden, in April, Karlsson is
expected to enter the 200 meters medley and relays and she may
also enter the 50 meters breaststroke, the event she won in 31.63
on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Australian swimmers dominated Sunday's session winning four
races.
</P>
<P>
Michael Klim won the men's 200 meters freestyle in 1:45.99;
Matthew Dunn got the 200 meters medley in 2:00.31; Adrian Radley
won the 200 meters backstroke in 1:59.47 and Natasha Bowron took
the women's 400 meters freestyle in 4:06.78. 
</P>
</TEXT>
