<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hi-Tech Industry Plays Major Role in Weihai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, January 27 (Xinhua) -- Latest statistics show that 297
high-tech industrial projects with total investment of 3.7 billion
yuan have been launched in the Weihai Hi-tech Industrial Zone in
east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
"This indicates the high-tech industry is now playing a major
role in the 40 square kilometer zone," said Li Guodong, director
of the zone's Administrative Commission.
</P>
<P>
At present, 77 percent of industrial projects carried out in
the zone involve high-tech operations, said Li.
</P>
<P>
The national-level zone, set up five years ago, has carried out
98 science research projects included in the outline of the State
Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the output of the hi-tech industries reached 2.1
billion yuan, accounting for 80 percent of the zone's total. And
the development of the high-tech industries helped raise its
import and export volume.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, 42 firms engaged in imports and exports had
been set up in Weihai, completing 580 million yuan of export
during the year.
</P>
<P>
Also last year, the number of research institutes and educated
personnel in the zone also increased by a large margin, and were
responsible for developing more than 40 high-tech products and
applied for patents for 63 projects.
</P>
<P>
To date, the zone has approved 866 projects, involving 11
billion yuan in total investment including 6.4 billion US dollars
in overseas investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
