<HEADLINE> Compagnoni Takes Women's Giant Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 26 (Xinhua) -- IDeborah Cumpagnoni finished an
all-Italian weekend sweep Sunday as she took the women's giant
slalom at the World Cup tournament in Cortina D'Ampezzo, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Compagnoni skiied a first run of one minute, 21.45 seconds and
a second run of 1:16.80 for a total time of 2:38.25 to win her
third title of the year, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Defending overall World Cup champion Katja Seizinger of Germany
was second with a combined time of 2:38.84, followed by Sonja Nef
of Switzerland, at 2:39.67.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Pernilla Wiberg, who currently owns a commanding
points lead in the overall championship standings, finished fourth.
</P>
<P>
Compagnoni's victory follows a win by countrywoman Isolde
Kostner in the super-G on Saturday and Kostner's sharing Friday's
downhill title with Zurbriggen -- only the second time in women's
World Cup history a downhill title has been shared.
</P>
<P>
The tour heads to Laax, Switzerland next weekend for downhill
and slalom events.  
</P>
